41
00:02:31,778 --> 00:02:34,823
(CHUCKLES) I'm sure I don't know.

42
00:02:35,573 --> 00:02:38,535
- (CHUCKLES) It's unusual, isn't it?
- (BREATHES DEEPLY)

43
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:40,578
My name's Oswald, what's yours?

44
00:02:40,745 --> 00:02:44,582
I don't have ice cream.
Why do you have ice cream?

45
00:02:45,416 --> 00:02:46,918
Please, by all means, you can--

46
00:02:47,085 --> 00:02:50,255
(YELLING) I don't have ice cream!

47
00:02:50,839 --> 00:02:53,049
Why do you have ice cream?

48
00:02:53,842 --> 00:02:55,468
I apologize, sir, I don't--

49
00:02:55,927 --> 00:02:57,095
Ah! (GRUNTS)

50
00:02:57,387 --> 00:02:59,848
- Excellent. No violent reaction.
- (INMATES TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

51
00:03:00,014 --> 00:03:03,393
The treatment is working perfectly.
Guards!

52
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,187
HELZINGER: <i>Where is my ice cream?
How come you have ice cream?</i>

53
00:03:06,354 --> 00:03:07,605
I want mine.

54
00:03:07,772 --> 00:03:10,024
- Where is it? Where is it?
